{
  "doc_id": "41848",
  "text": "In 2012, Zhang et al. [CITATION_1] proposed the CT algorithm, which provided a concise and efficient solution for real-time visual tracking applications. The primary innovation of the CT algorithm was the compressive sensing-based random feature extraction method. Benefiting from this fast and effective way to compress raw pixel data, the CT algorithm succeeded in excellent real-time performance. [CITATION_2] Meanwhile, the online learning Naïve Bayes classifier used for separating the target from background, which is a simple but effective pattern recognition method, ensured the tracking robustness to disturbances like appearance changes, camera vibration, and so on. [CITATION_3] Because the CT algorithm found a balance point between the real-time performance and effectiveness, it has a bright future in low-power realtime computer vision applications.",
